repository-code: "https://github.com/mos-ks/MUHA"
url: "https://mos-ks.github.io/MUHA/"
abstract: >-
  We study the effect of exposing model-estimated spatial uncertainty to
  annotators via a purpose-built interface, directing their attention to
  objects whose boundaries are deemed unreliable. In a randomized
  controlled study with 120 participants across 1,800 annotation trials on
  autonomous driving images, participants receiving uncertainty cues
  achieved higher label quality (0.70 mIoU %-point improvement) and were
  faster overall (7.2%). The findings establish localization uncertainty
  as a practical lever for improving human-in-the-loop annotation wherever
  model-assisted review involves spatial outputs.
keywords:
  - data annotation
  - human-AI decision-making
  - localization uncertainty
  - object detection
  - autonomous driving
license: MIT
